<tr>
<th style="background:#fee8ab;">Languages</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<p><b>Spoken &amp; written script of holy <a href="/wiki/Guru_Granth_Sahib" title="Guru Granth Sahib">Guru Granth Sahib</a>:</b><br />
Written language of the Sri Guru Granth Sahib: <a href="/wiki/Gurmukhi" title="Gurmukhi" class="mw-redirect">Gurmukhi</a></p>
<p>Spoken words: mostly <a href="/wiki/Punjabi_language" title="Punjabi language">Punjabi</a>, with <a href="/wiki/Brij_Bhasha" title="Brij Bhasha">Brij Bhasha</a>, Sahiskriti, <a href="/wiki/Sant_Bhasha" title="Sant Bhasha">Sant Bhasha</a><sup id="cite_ref-20" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-20" title=""><span>[</span>21<span>]</span></a></sup><br />
and <a href="/wiki/Persian_Language" title="Persian Language" class="mw-redirect">Persian</a><sup id="cite_ref-21" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-21" title=""><span>[</span>22<span>]</span></a></sup><br />
, languages of other contributing non-Sikh Pirs</p>
<p><b>Predominant <a href="/wiki/Spoken_language" title="Spoken language">spoken languages</a>:</b></p>
The <a href="/wiki/Vernacular" title="Vernacular">vernacular</a> language of the home nation in the Sikh diaspora, significantly including <a href="/wiki/Punjabi_language" title="Punjabi language">Punjabi</a>, <a href="/wiki/English_language" title="English language">English</a>, <a href="/wiki/Hindi" title="Hindi">Hindi</a>, <a href="/wiki/Urdu" title="Urdu">Urdu</a>, <a href="/wiki/Swahili_language" title="Swahili language">Swahili</a>, <a href="/wiki/Malay_language" title="Malay language">Malay</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Thai_language" title="Thai language">Thai</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
